1
00:00:09,410 --> 00:00:14,520
We were suddenly faced with the reality of death.

2
00:00:16,057 --> 00:00:18,685
So you all know about Madoka?

3
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:21,955
Yes, Meguru filled us in.

4
00:00:24,690 --> 00:00:27,250
We haven't even buried her ashes.

5
00:00:27,961 --> 00:00:32,740
But with the situation as it is, a grave is the least of our worries.

6
00:01:00,610 --> 00:01:02,250
Madoka.

7
00:01:04,820 --> 00:01:06,830
I reunited with him.

8
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:14,670
Yuma,

9
00:01:14,670 --> 00:01:16,790
do you have a minute?

10
00:01:16,790 --> 00:01:18,290
Me?

11
00:01:19,263 --> 00:01:20,433
Yes.

12
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:30,120
Come on in.

13
00:01:39,266 --> 00:01:42,820
This is my sister's room.

14
00:01:43,290 --> 00:01:45,070
I see.

15
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:49,700
Take a look at this.

16
00:01:53,077 --> 00:01:58,370
[Dear Kagami Madoka]

17
00:01:58,370 --> 00:02:00,110
[Hirose Yuma]

18
00:02:00,110 --> 00:02:02,230
These are all letters I sent.

19
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,190
Exactly.

20
00:02:06,050 --> 00:02:08,110
I managed

21
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:10,630
to find yours.

22
00:02:13,347 --> 00:02:15,320
My sister was always

23
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:18,220
the meticulous type.

24
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,620
She made sure to preserve...

25
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:24,960
every fan letter she got.

26
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:33,140
So she actually read them.

27
00:02:36,650 --> 00:02:38,290
She did.

28
00:02:41,730 --> 00:02:44,270
Looks like you sent her plenty.

29
00:02:47,050 --> 00:02:48,790
Thank you.

30
00:03:06,410 --> 00:03:07,900
Yuma...

31
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:14,820
I beg you...

32
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:19,100
Please never forget my sister.

33
00:03:21,642 --> 00:03:23,432
I'm counting on you.

34
00:03:25,890 --> 00:03:27,870
I won't.

35
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:31,890
I promise I won't.

36
00:03:39,230 --> 00:03:48,090
[The End Of The World With You]

37
00:03:52,117 --> 00:03:57,120
[Finale: Longing for a Miracle at Life's End]

38
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,741
Sorry for taking your family's car.

39
00:03:59,741 --> 00:04:02,590
It's fine. We won't be able to do much with it during these three days.

40
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:03,753
Thank you, sir.

41
00:04:03,753 --> 00:04:06,333
Nothing beats a car.

42
00:04:07,397 --> 00:04:09,890
Anyone knows these dudes?

43
00:04:09,890 --> 00:04:11,560
I don't know them.

44
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:14,430
They've been at it for days.

45
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:16,720
I can't blame them.

46
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,520
Hey!

47
00:04:22,030 --> 00:04:25,120
I've got some goodies for you all.

48
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:27,067
Shove off, man!

49
00:04:27,067 --> 00:04:29,137
What the hell!

50
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:38,760
Watch out!

51
00:04:54,962 --> 00:04:56,740
You're okay?

52
00:04:56,740 --> 00:04:58,430
Are you hurt?

53
00:04:59,610 --> 00:05:01,130
N-No, I'm fine.

54
00:05:04,104 --> 00:05:05,580
Ritsu...

55
00:05:06,157 --> 00:05:08,147
you saw that, didn't you?

56
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,780
Alright, let's head out.

57
00:05:20,621 --> 00:05:22,220
Thanks for the souvenirs.

58
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:24,253
Share them amongst yourselves, okay?

59
00:05:24,253 --> 00:05:25,663
Will do.

60
00:05:32,690 --> 00:05:34,290
One more thing.

61
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,890
Here.

62
00:05:47,081 --> 00:05:50,010
Your contact info?
[LIME : meguru 409 /
Stant telegram @ melty.kiss.409.xox]

63
00:05:50,010 --> 00:05:52,940
If a miracle occurs,

64
00:05:52,940 --> 00:05:55,533
and everything goes back to normal,

65
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:57,083
text me, okay?

66
00:05:58,830 --> 00:06:00,620
Meguru...

67
00:06:03,063 --> 00:06:04,640
I...

68
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:08,850
I want to see you again too. No, we definitely will!

69
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:12,180
The meteor won't come. We sent our energy, remember?

70
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:15,410
Yes, you're right.

71
00:06:15,410 --> 00:06:19,350
Ritsu, you didn't join in last time, did you? Come on! Join us!

72
00:06:19,350 --> 00:06:21,150
Seriously?

73
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:24,890
Ready? Go away, you damn meteor!

74
00:06:25,460 --> 00:06:27,200
G-Go away, you damn meteor...

75
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,773
Go away, you damn meteor!

76
00:06:28,773 --> 00:06:32,259
- G-Go away, you damn meteor...
- Go away, you damn meteor!

77
00:06:32,259 --> 00:06:34,962
Okay, enough of that. Let's go.

78
00:06:49,020 --> 00:06:52,960
See you! Let's reunite one day, okay?

79
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:55,310
Yes, it's a promise!

80
00:06:55,310 --> 00:06:56,850
Bye bye!

81
00:06:56,850 --> 00:07:00,570
See you around, Meguru!

82
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:12,010
Thank you...

83
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:14,640
Thank you for everything, guys.

84
00:07:26,020 --> 00:07:31,750
[September 22nd, 2023 / 4:45 PM]

85
00:07:34,621 --> 00:07:37,035
Is your place around here?

86
00:07:37,035 --> 00:07:41,150
Yes. You can drop me off at the floating torii gate coming up.
[T/N: A shrine gate built on the ocean]

87
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:42,260
You're sure?

88
00:07:42,261 --> 00:07:43,600
We'll drive you home.

89
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:47,990
No need. It's a quick walk from there.

90
00:07:47,990 --> 00:07:49,428
I see.

91
00:07:51,297 --> 00:07:52,710
You know,

92
00:07:52,710 --> 00:07:54,600
Something just came back to me.

93
00:07:58,110 --> 00:07:59,800
What now?

94
00:08:00,714 --> 00:08:03,860
So I've been thinking...

95
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:05,410
Yes?

96
00:08:05,930 --> 00:08:09,230
When Meguru called me out...

97
00:08:11,459 --> 00:08:14,270
she was actually trying to confess to me,

98
00:08:14,728 --> 00:08:16,346
right?

99
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:31,590
What?

100
00:08:31,590 --> 00:08:33,440
Oh, take a left up there.

101
00:08:43,410 --> 00:08:44,920
Thank you.

102
00:08:46,127 --> 00:08:48,160
That's that.

103
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,600
See you.

104
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:52,960
Hold on!

105
00:08:53,857 --> 00:08:55,430
Why?

106
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:58,590
I don't want this to be depressing.

107
00:08:58,590 --> 00:09:00,110
Sounds good?

108
00:09:02,820 --> 00:09:05,710
Alright, have it your way.

109
00:09:07,381 --> 00:09:08,830
Yuma.

110
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:12,060
Sorry about all this, really.

111
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:14,221
It's all good.

112
00:09:14,221 --> 00:09:16,610
Besides, I got to meet Meguru,

113
00:09:16,610 --> 00:09:19,380
and find closure on Maataso.

114
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,490
All in all, it was a fun journey.

115
00:09:29,217 --> 00:09:30,770
Hey!

116
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:34,274
Ritsu, Masumi, see you later.

117
00:09:34,274 --> 00:09:36,110
And that's a promise, okay?

118
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:41,260
Don't trust strangers online anymore.

119
00:09:49,923 --> 00:09:51,620
You know...

120
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:53,070
Yes?

121
00:09:53,630 --> 00:09:56,500
What is he?

122
00:09:58,198 --> 00:10:03,360
Let's not think about it. I'm not too good with the occult.

123
00:10:04,147 --> 00:10:06,539
But you saw what I saw, right?

124
00:10:06,539 --> 00:10:08,847
He really must be...

125
00:10:09,930 --> 00:10:13,800
some sort of supernatural miracle boy.

126
00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:18,480
Even if he is,

127
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:22,060
do you think he can deal with a meteor?

128
00:10:32,530 --> 00:10:34,240
Well, we won't find out

129
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,998
until the time comes.

130
00:10:42,487 --> 00:10:45,010
Today's the 22nd.

131
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:49,180
We have one full day tomorrow

132
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:53,130
until the meteor hits on the morning of the 24th.

133
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:02,790
Here.

134
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:05,500
It's going to get cold.

135
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,200
Thanks.

136
00:11:08,090 --> 00:11:09,643
Good thing we have a car.

137
00:11:09,643 --> 00:11:13,343
Agreed. Anything beats our outdoors experience yesterday.

138
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:18,890
What shall we do tomorrow? I don't mind staying in Hamamatsu.

139
00:11:20,781 --> 00:11:23,540
How about returning to Tokyo?

140
00:11:23,540 --> 00:11:25,590
I'd like to settle down somewhere familiar.

141
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:29,390
Then my place is a no-go.

142
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:32,340
Stairs are the last thing your leg can handle.

143
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:41,040
In that case, how about mine?

144
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:43,676
That is, if you don't mind the cramped space.

145
00:11:46,607 --> 00:11:52,240
Wait a second, we both assumed we'd be together.

146
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,060
Did I get my hopes up?

147
00:12:00,870 --> 00:12:02,810
No, you didn't.

148
00:12:04,210 --> 00:12:06,040
Thank god.

149
00:12:20,810 --> 00:12:23,100
You're getting cold.

150
00:12:28,530 --> 00:12:30,550
Then warm me up.

151
00:12:35,270 --> 00:12:36,960
Sure.

152
00:13:28,220 --> 00:13:32,560
Touch me.

153
00:13:37,618 --> 00:13:39,940
Doesn't your leg hurt?

154
00:13:39,940 --> 00:13:42,400
Besides, it's cramped.

155
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,680
If it gets knocked around...

156
00:13:46,393 --> 00:13:50,816
We might die the day after tomorrow.

157
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,790
Fine, whatever.

158
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,280
Masumi.

159
00:14:14,850 --> 00:14:17,360
I just don't want to push you.

160
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:20,620
I'm worried about you, okay?

161
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:32,070
If I had it my way, I'd be doing you all day.

162
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:44,520
Does that feel good?

163
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:46,390
Yes.

164
00:14:55,330 --> 00:14:57,650
I felt content.

165
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:09,250
Let's do this properly when we get back, OK?

166
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:19,190
Regardless of my impending death.

167
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:39,500
[September 23rd, 2023 / 11:00 AM]

168
00:15:40,174 --> 00:15:43,050
We finally made it back.

169
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:44,730
Yes.

170
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:58,030
You know, I was planning on selling my apartment anyway.

171
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:00,010
Your place?

172
00:16:00,770 --> 00:16:02,460
Yes.

173
00:16:04,431 --> 00:16:07,410
My company wasn't doing so well,

174
00:16:07,410 --> 00:16:12,140
and as their sponsor, I was to take the blame, debt and all.

175
00:16:12,140 --> 00:16:13,933
I see.

176
00:16:15,342 --> 00:16:18,520
Either way, my future looked bleak.

177
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:20,820
Of course I would want to die.

178
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,670
But now?

179
00:16:31,630 --> 00:16:34,780
Now I feel like I would make it work out.

180
00:16:48,342 --> 00:16:52,680
Remember how we reunited at the library?

181
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,313
Of course I do.

182
00:16:54,313 --> 00:16:59,186
You came to return an overdue book. What a coincidence, huh?

183
00:16:59,186 --> 00:17:01,776
Sorry, that was a lie.

184
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:05,520
I was actually waiting for you.

185
00:17:07,794 --> 00:17:09,720
Huh?

186
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:11,500
What do you mean?

187
00:17:12,180 --> 00:17:16,240
Back in college, you told me about your ideal way of going out.

188
00:17:20,073 --> 00:17:26,530
You said if Earth were to end tomorrow, you'd pass time by reading in the library.

189
00:17:30,820 --> 00:17:33,390
Did I?

190
00:17:34,260 --> 00:17:36,450
You don't remember?

191
00:17:38,492 --> 00:17:40,700
Because I do.

192
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:43,320
I remember all our little moments together, Masumi.

193
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:50,350
And although it was a baseless assumption,

194
00:17:51,910 --> 00:17:54,080
you were actually there.

195
00:17:56,510 --> 00:18:00,730
For that alone, I'll thank our friend Mr. Meteor.

196
00:18:09,470 --> 00:18:11,630
I'm really glad...

197
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:15,680
I got to reunite with you.

198
00:18:46,290 --> 00:18:49,230
I'm sure life will throw us hell...

199
00:18:51,210 --> 00:18:54,260
even if we survive.

200
00:19:06,780 --> 00:19:08,750
Still...

201
00:19:13,550 --> 00:19:15,920
I want to live on,

202
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:20,220
if it means a future with you.

203
00:19:49,340 --> 00:19:52,330
It didn't feel like the first time in ten years.

204
00:19:53,227 --> 00:19:55,050
Right there...

205
00:19:55,050 --> 00:19:57,190
Shit...!

206
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:12,465
You haven't changed one bit, Masumi.

207
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,610
Ritsu...

208
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:31,660
I would never have imagined ten days ago...

209
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:38,280
that I'd be messing around with you again.

210
00:20:55,940 --> 00:21:04,640
♫ Our shadows come close, as if reminiscing ♫

211
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:14,930
♫ I stopped, unable to touch your cheek ♫

212
00:21:14,930 --> 00:21:24,360
♫ I'll no longer regret those days long past ♫

213
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:32,170
♫ For I'll always remember them ♫

214
00:21:32,170 --> 00:21:33,860
Masumi.

215
00:21:38,220 --> 00:21:40,150
What is it?

216
00:21:41,630 --> 00:21:44,600
Thank you...

217
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:49,350
for sticking with me until the end.

218
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:55,230
♫ This very moment, is my everything ♫

219
00:21:58,300 --> 00:22:00,010
Of course.

220
00:22:11,298 --> 00:22:13,658
I guess miracles...

221
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,500
do exist.

